  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The study examines time spent in the emergency room on admission of patients with hip
      fracture in a cohort with a traditional setup compared with a prospective cohort with a fast
      track admission schedule including nurse initiation of treatmnet, standardized analgesia,
      fluid and oxygen therapy and standardized logistics for x-ray and admission procedures.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
